---
const { data: d } = Astro.props;
---
<div class="dp-callout dp-callout--gotcha">
  <p class="dp-callout__title">🚧 This page is being written</p>
  <p>The full walkthrough — analogy, diagrams, idiomatic Go, trade-offs and a quiz — is on its way. Here's the gist for now.</p>
</div>

{d.nutshell && (
  <Fragment>
    <h2 id="in-a-nutshell">In a nutshell</h2>
    <p>{d.nutshell}</p>
  </Fragment>
)}

<h2 id="whats-coming">What you'll find here</h2>
<ul>
  <li>The problem this {d.kind === 'guide' ? 'topic' : 'pattern'} solves, with a memorable real-world analogy</li>
  <li>A UML structure diagram and a step-by-step sequence diagram</li>
  <li>
    An idiomatic Go implementation{d.source ? (
      <Fragment> — <a href={d.source} target="_blank" rel="noopener">browse the source on GitHub</a></Fragment>
    ) : ''}
  </li>
  <li>How Go's interfaces &amp; composition reshape the classic design</li>
  <li>Where it shows up in the Go standard library</li>
  <li>When to use it, when to avoid it, and a quick self-check quiz</li>
</ul>
